- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with orderings and antichains, which are concepts related to data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with coverability and termination, which are topics related to automata theory. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the abstract handling of orderings, which could be relevant to software engineering.
